Hi devs! üëã

Welcome to the August edition of our **Developer News**! We've got some exciting updates to share with you this month! üöÄ üì∞
# üíª Platform Updates
*For more details on recent developer updates, including new AutoMod rules and message forwarding in the API, check out our [developer change log](https://discord.com/developers/docs/change-log).*
## üöÄ User-installed Apps
Great news! User-installed apps are now generally available, bringing a set of [API changes and improvements](https://discord.com/developers/docs/change-log#june-27-2024-api-updates). 
- These apps can now post non-ephemeral replies in small servers and can be eligible for app discovery surfaces like the App Directory.
We've also introduced a new [**Use External Apps**](https://discord.com/developers/docs/change-log#june-27-2024-new-use-external-apps-permission) permission, allowing modmins to control whether user-installed apps can post public replies in a server. Plus, you can now see an approximate user install count in the [Application object](https://discord.com/developers/docs/resources/application#application-object) and in your [app's settings](https://discord.com/developers/applications) !
## üíé Premium Apps Updates
We've rolled out several exciting features for Premium Apps:
- A new [premium button style](https://discord.com/developers/docs/interactions/message-components#button-object-button-styles) for linking to specific SKUs in your Store
- Deep linking capabilities to [specific SKUs](https://discord.com/developers/docs/monetization/skus#linking-to-your-skus) or [directly to your Store](https://discord.com/developers/docs/monetization/managing-your-store#linking-to-your-store)
- A [customizable Store page](https://discord.com/developers/docs/monetization/managing-your-store#adding-skus-to-your-store) within the developer portal to showcase your app subscriptions and one-time purchase items
- New Subscription HTTP API Endpoints and Subscription Gateway Events. Check out the [reference docs for Subscriptions](https://discord.com/developers/docs/monetization/implementing-app-subscriptions#using-the-subscription-api).
üö®¬†Heads up! We have some upcoming changes to how Entitlements behave. If you're using monetization in your app, be sure to check out the [change log and migration guide](https://discord.com/developers/docs/change-log#premium-apps-entitlement-migration-and-new-subscription-api) to see how it might impact your app. 
## üòÑ App Emojis
Express yourself with app emojis! You can now upload up to 2000 emojis for your application [using the API](https://discord.com/developers/docs/resources/emoji#list-application-emojis) or in your [app's settings](https://discord.com/developers/applications). Use these custom emojis anywhere on Discord!
# üéÆ New Case Studies and [discord.com/build](http://discord.com/build) Makeover
We've given [**discord.com/build**](http://discord.com/build) a fresh new look, showcasing the many possibilities for developers on Discord's platform. Along with this update, we've published [three new case studies](https://discord.com/build#case-studies) featuring a few of our Activities partners: 
- üî´ FRVR: Scaling and Monetizing Krunker Strike on Discord
- ü§ñ Playroom: Building and Scaling a Multiplayer AI Game on Discord
- üßë‚Äçüç≥ Mojiworks: Creating Your First Discord Activity
**Ready to start building?** Check out our [Embedded App SDK](https://discord.com/developers/docs/activities/overview#public-developer-preview) and begin crafting your own interactive experiences today!

We're thrilled about these updates and can't wait to see what you'll create next on Discord! üöÄ
üíú Your Discord Developer team 
-# *Server admins, if you'd like to change which channel should receive our Developer News or opt-out at any time, you can do so in the [Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/active-developer) or by editing your announcement channel's integrations settings, depending on how you subscribed.*

Hey Admins and Mods! Starting May 15, it's possible you might notice something new next to some of your members' usernames: ‚ú® **Guild Tags **‚ú®

See a cute little tag next to a member's username or profile? That's a **Guild Tag**, which indicates someone's membership to a chosen Guild. What this means for you, beloved Admins and Mods, is that if your server's AutoMod is on, it will also check for Guild Tags ‚òëÔ∏è 

**What's a Guild?** It's a small, exclusive server that members can apply to join. These servers are tight-knit communities where members can relish in shared identities, hobbies, play styles, and more!

Much love,

# üíª Platform Updates
## ü§© User-Installed Apps in Preview
Apps can now be installed to user accounts, making them easier to install, discover, and access across Discord. By default, user-installed apps can be used across all of a user's servers, within their (G)DMs, and in DMs with an app's bot user. Apps can be updated to support user installation on the new Installation page in your [app's settings](<https://discord.com/developers/applications>). 

**During the preview, interaction responses for the user installation context will be forced to be ephemeral in servers with over 25 members.** We are running a [limited experiment](<https://discord.com/channels/613425648685547541/697138785317814292/1229541866220028015>) in our DDevs community where this limitation is lifted. There also may be changes to the new fields discussed in the change log before general availability. 

Read all the technical details, limitations, and known issues in the [change log](<https://discord.com/developers/docs/change-log#userinstallable-apps-preview>), or follow the [tutorial](<https://discord.com/developers/docs/tutorials/developing-a-user-installable-app>) to get started.
## üìä CSV Export for Premium App Analytics
We heard you like numbers, so If you have an app with [Monetization](<https://discord.com/developers/docs/monetization/overview>) enabled you can now export your SKU analytics to CSV. This will allow you to use your preferred data tools to report on your premium offerings.

You can find the export at the bottom of the Monetization ‚Üí Analytics tab of your app to export datapoints such as `sales_count`, `sales_amount`, `sales_currencies`, `cancellation_count`, `refund_amount`, and `refund_count`, aggregated by each of your offerings for the selected month.

As we bask in the glow of India's 75th Republic Day, there's a genuine sense of joy seeing how far our nation has come. #  Marketplace Guidelines

---

##  General Posting Guidelines

1. **Be Respectful**: Treat everyone with respect, and communicate professionally.
2. **Stay on Topic**: Post in the appropriate channels (e.g., use **Client** tag for hiring and **#Freelancer** tag for offering services).
3. **No Spam**: Avoid repetitive posts or promoting unrelated services.
4. **No Scams or Misleading Posts**: Only post genuine opportunities or services; scams will lead to a permanent ban.

---

## üíº For Clients  ‚Äì Posting Guidelines

**Channel**: `#Client`

1. **Job Title**: Start with a clear job title (e.g., "Need a custom economy discord bot ").
2. **Project Details**: Provide a short description of the project or work needed.
3. **Payment Terms**: Indicate whether it‚Äôs hourly, project-based, or other, and the payment method (e.g., PayPal, bank transfer or crypto etc).
4. **Deadline**: Mention any deadlines for the project, if applicable.
5. **Contact Information**: Include your preferred contact method (e.g., Discord DMs, email).

> **Example Post**:  
> 
> ### **Job Title**: Need a Custom Economy Discord Bot  
> **Details**: Looking for someone to create a Discord bot with a custom economy system, including commands for earning, spending, and leaderboard functionality.  
> **Skills**: Proficient in JavaScript or Python, experience with Discord.js or Discord.py  
> **Payment**: $50, PayPal or bank transfer  
> **Deadline**: Complete within 2 weeks  
> **Contact**: email => krishna.js@proton.me or DM @wireguard.

---
> **Example Post**:  
> 
> ### **Service**: Discord Bot Development  
> **Skills and Experience**: 3 years in Discord Development, proficient in Discord.js and Node.js  
> **Portfolio**: [Link to Portfolio](https://github.com/krishnassh/)  
> **Rates**: Project-based, starting at $50 per bot (prices may vary based on complexity)  
> **Availability**: Available to start immediately  
> **Contact**: DM @wireguard. or email at krishna.js@proton.me

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Additional Tips
- **Keep It Professional**: Use proper language and avoid excessive emojis or CAPS.
- **Updates**: If your job or service is no longer available, please edit or delete your post.

---

Thank you for reading!
